\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 Investigations}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~deal largely with the difficulties of language and\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meaning_(philosophy_of_language)"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 meaning}}{\f0\fs24\b0 . Wittgenstein viewed the tools of language as being fundamentally simple\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philosophical_Investigations#cite_note-6"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\super [}}{\f0\fs24\b0\ul\ulc0\super\cf4 a]}{\f0\fs24\b0\super [}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:No_original_research#Primary,_secondary_and_tertiary_sources"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i1\super non-primary source needed}}{\f0\fs24\b0\super ]}{\f0\fs24\b0 , and he believed that philosophers had obscured this simplicity by misusing language and by asking meaningless questions. He attempted in the\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 Investigations}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~to make things clear: "}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 Der Fliege den Ausweg aus dem Fliegenglas zeigen}{\f0\fs24\b0 "\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 to show the fly the way out of the\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fly_bottle"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 fly bottle}}{\f0\fs24\b0 .}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philosophical_Investigations#cite_note-7"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\super [}}{\f0\fs24\b0\ul\ulc0\super\cf4 6]}{ }
