\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 Hacker in general finds many received components of current\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philosophy_of_mind"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 philosophy of mind}}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~to be incoherent. He rejects\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Type_physicalism"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 mind-brain identity theories}}{\f0\fs24\b0 , as well as\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Functionalism_(philosophy_of_mind)"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 functionalism}}{\f0\fs24\b0 ,\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eliminative_materialism"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 eliminativism}}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~and other forms of\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reductionism"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 reductionism}}{\f0\fs24\b0 . He advocates\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Methodological_pluralism"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 methodological pluralism}}{\f0\fs24\b0 , denying that standard explanations of human conduct are causal, and insisting on the irreducibility of explanation in terms of reasons and goals. He denies that psychological attributes can be intelligibly ascribed to the brain, insisting that they are ascribable only to the human being as a whole. He has endeavoured to show that the puzzles and 'mysteries' of consciousness dissolve under careful analysis of the various forms of intransitive and transitive\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Consciousness"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 consciousness}}{\f0\fs24\b0 , and that so-called\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qualia"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 qualia}}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~are no more than a philosopher's fiction.}{ }
